15 (b)(1) Within 24 hours of the birth of a newborn infant, a licensed general hospital or
16 birthing center shall make available to such newborn infant's parent or guardian a video
17 presentation on water safety education to be viewed onsite.
18 (2) Such hospital and birthing center shall provide such parent or guardian with a water
19 safety education form to be developed by the department. Such form shall be signed and
20 dated by the parent or guardian and shall include whether the parent or guardian viewed
21 the video presentation or refused to do so. Upon completion, such form shall be provided
22 to and maintained by the department.
23 (c) The department shall promulgate rules and regulations necessary to implement the
24 provisions of this Code section."
25 SECTION 2.
26 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
